<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-09-22T16:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-09-22T16:14:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.61334/135: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bading</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-22T16:00:00-05:14"><hi rend="italic">September 22,
                                        1924—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:15
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>14. Department’s telegram 16, September 16, noon. I have received direct
                            assurance from the President that the Mercantile Bank matter will be
                            arranged satisfactorily. The President favors last year’s bill providing
                            for liquidation of the Association and continuation of tax, and is
                            opposed to budget article providing for denial of obligation of the
                            state after December 31st, 1925.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bading</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>